KW  - Real business cycle models
KW  - Externalities
KW  - Sunspots
KW  - Observational equivalence
AB  - This paper points out that real business cycle models are observationally equivalent to externality models, which we define as models with externalities and sunspots but without productivity shocks. As far as standard first-order systems are concerned, however, externality models turn out to be more flexible than RBC models. This explains, at least partly, why previous studies have found that externality models perform better than standard RBC models at generating realistic business cycle behavior. Our results cast doubt on the arguments of Farmer and Guo (1994) and Caballero and Lyons (1992).
